<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, 
regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author&#8217;s surname, given name. &#34;Title of Paper.&#34; In <em>Title of Conference Proceedings</em>, edited by Editor&#8217;s name (name in normal order), page numbers of chapter. Place of publication: Publisher, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Cooper, Agatha</span>. 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Paper">Appalachian Mountain Clog Dancing</span>.&#34; In 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Conference Proceedings">Proceedings of the Society of Ethnomusicology and Dance Conference</span></em>, 
	edited by <span class="hover" title="Editor&#8217;s name">Brian A. Brown</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers of chapter">123&#45;47</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">Auckland</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Society of Ethnomusicology and Dance</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>.
</blockquote>
